ated bodies. 83. The method of claim 81 , wherein said at least one or more benchmark standards comprises at least one clinical diagnosis that has been independently verified to be accurate in identifying said mental state. 84. The method of claim 81 , wherein said speech data is received substantially in real-time as said subject is speaking. 85. The method of claim 81 , wherein said speech data is produced in an offline mode from a stored recording of said subjectâs speech. 86. A method for processing speech data of a subject to identify a mental state of said subject, comprising: receiving said speech data of said subject; and using at least one processing technique to process said speech data to identify said mental state, wherein said identification of said mental state is better according to one or more performance metrics as compared to a standardized mental health questionnaire or testing tool usable for identifying said mental state. 87. The method of claim 86, wherein said one or more performance metrics comprise a sensitivity or specificity, and wherein said speech data is processed according to a desired level of sensitivity or a desired level of specificity. 88. The method of claim 87, wherein said desired level of sensitivity or said desired level of specificity is defined based on criteria established by an entity. 89. The method of claim 88, wherein said entity comprises one or more of the following: clinicians, healthcare providers, personal caregivers, insurance companies, and government-regulated bodies. 90. A method for processing speech data of a subject to identify or assess a mental state of said subject, comprising: receiving said speech data of said subject; and using one or more processing technique to process said speech data to generate one or more descriptors indicative of said mental state; and 

